          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1684425176368-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your<strong> gochujang paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to a small bowl with your <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>,<strong> </strong>the<strong> remaining chopped garlic</strong>,<strong> cornflour</strong> and 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up, then add 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[65ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [80ml] </span><strong>warm water</strong> and stir it all together until smooth – this is your<strong> gochujang stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1684425192848-x200.jpg",
